"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-showbiz-tv-radio-1934486-olympic-viewers-switch-off-breakdancing-debut\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"For the first time inOlympichistory, breakdancing was shown on the Paris Summer Games by the International Olympic Committee, but people are still divided.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 93, \"end\": 124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"16 women and 15 men travelled to theFrenchcapital in hopes of becoming the first person to win Gold in the sport, however, the first match went viral for the wrong reasons.\", \"from\": 157, \"to\": 329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Friday, Australia's Raygun found herself in a social media storm after her performance left fans questioning whether breakdancing should be an Olympic sport.\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 342, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9931708980845764, \"rank\": 0.003359610772615643, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 354, \"end\": 360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.490067160191886e-24, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 36-year-old went viral after awkwardly squirming across the dancefloor with a chaotic routine which ended without a single score from the judges.\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 642, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the contest continued with appearances from athletes hailing from theUSA,Japan, Lituania andChina, viewers revealed they were too \\\"cringed\\\" to continue watching.\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9996715457544741, \"rank\": 0.00018173689187848737, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Noah Lyles left red-faced after USA relay horror show as Michael Johnson fumes    An unimpressed @OwenReeman3 stated: \\\"It's been here less than a day and I already hate it Get Breakdancing out of the Olympics as soon as possible because wtf is this.\\\"\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 852, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8782531984627681, \"rank\": 0.13827691881949458, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"score\": 0.6562406956374156, \"rank\": 0.2753288987434648, \"text\": \"Michael Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(sic)  Taking to X, @TheTweetingElf admitted: \\\"I had to stop watching the break dancing.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 115